com.kontakt.sdk.android.cloud.api.executor.configs

Class ReadAllRequestExecutor

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.kontakt.sdk.android.cloud.api.executor.RequestExecutor<T>
      • com.kontakt.sdk.android.cloud.api.executor.PaginatedRequestExecutor<Configs>
        • com.kontakt.sdk.android.cloud.api.executor.configs.ReadAllRequestExecutor

  • public class ReadAllRequestExecutor
extends PaginatedRequestExecutor<Configs>
    Request executor provided by ConfigsApi. Use this class if you want to obtain READ_ALL encrypted commands through fluent API in chained fashion. Here is an example of how to use this executor: 
       
   KontaktCloud kontaktCloud = KontaktCloudFactory.create();
   Configs configs = kontaktCloud.configs().readAll()
      .withIds("7HuT", "2Fge", "dFGh")
      .maxResult(10)
      .execute();
